the south african foreign affairs department which handles 
relations with the four black homelands established by south 
africas whitedominated government said it had asked 
bophuthatswana about the allegations and was awaiting a replay 
sebogodi on behalf of braklaagtes 9000 residents went to 
court last year to try to nullify the south african governments 
declaration that braklaagte would be placed under the jurisdiction 
of bophuthatswana he said his people faced hardship and 
discrimination if the community was incorporated into the homeland 
