the incorporation is part of south africas policy of locating 
black ethnic groups in selfgoverning homelands to limit the size 
of the black population in the rest of south africa 
the homelands are not recognized internationally 
bophuthatswana includes seven separate pieces of territory 
covering about 18000 square miles and has a population estimated 
at 17 million 
