<TEXT>
a combined force of leftist guerrillas and 
drug traffickers overran a jungle police post in the heart of 
perus cocaine region killing 10 officers and wounding 12 
military officials reported tuesday 
the attack at dusk monday was among the bloodiest of recent 
months officials said it may have been a response to usfinanced 
testing of a powerful herbicide against coca the raw material of 
cocaine 
premier armando villanueva and defense minister enrique lopez 
flew to uchiza site of the attack 245 miles northeast of lima on 
tuesday the government news agency andina reported officials said 
more than 100 soldiers and police troopers were sent to the town as 
reinforcements 
in june 1987 drug traffickers and maoist guerrillas of the 
shining path destroyed the police post at uchiza in the cocaine 
country of perus huallaga valley six policemen were killed in 
that raid 
shining path guerrillas has provided protection to drug 
traffickers for about two years in exchange for arms and money 
they began their insurgency in 1980 in the region around ayachuco 
in the andes 
military officials said 150 rebels and drugrunners attacked the 
50man post monday with gunfire and grenades they said surviving 
defenders fled into the surrounding jungle 
six attackers were slain and their companions carried the bodies 
away the officials said on condition of anonymity 
they said telephone connections with uchiza were cut and word of 
the attack reached lima hours later by radio still with sketchy 
details 
ten days ago the us and peruvian governments began a second 
phase of tests of the herbacide tebuthiuron sold under the name 
spike in the huallaga valley which produces about 60 percent of 
the worlds coca 
environmentalists say the chemical could destroy other plants 
and lead to widespread erosion officials said tests on 40 acres 
would track the herbicides effects on coca and the environment 
over at least a year 
coca produced in the uchiza region is partially processed in 
jungle laboratories and flown from clandestine airstrips to 
colombia where it is refined into cocaine for sale in us and 
european markets 
