constitutionally obligated to send him back to alabama for trial 
eilperin said 
fisher argued however that alabama authorities cannot certify 
om for trial as an adult and subject him to a possible death 
sentence without him first being returned to the state 
an extradition order he said thus would violate the districts 
ban on capital punishment because it would clear the way for 
alabama authorities to try om as an adult should they so chose 
